hh3cDSP.name: hh3cDSP

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

hh3cDSP.contactinfo: PLAT Team Hangzhou H3C Technologies Co.,Ltd. Shang-Di Information Industry Base, Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cDSP.description: This MIB is to provide the definition of the DSP(Digital Signal Processing) status.

hh3cVPMStatusTable.name: hh3cVPMStatusTable
hh3cVPMStatusTable.description: The table contains status parameters of VPM(Voice Process Module) card.

hh3cVPMStatusEntry.name: hh3cVPMStatusEntry
hh3cVPMStatusEntry.description: The entry of VPM status table.

hh3cVPMIndex.name: hh3cVPMIndex
hh3cVPMIndex.description: The index for this entry. The sequence of VPM card in the chassis is from the top to bottom.

hh3cVPMEnPhysicalIndex.name: hh3cVPMEnPhysicalIndex
hh3cVPMEnPhysicalIndex.description: The object corresponds to PhysicalIndex in the chassis.

hh3cVPMState.name: hh3cVPMState
hh3cVPMState.description: The object indicates the current state of VPM card being monitored. normal(1) - VPM card in normal condition. warning(2) - VPM card has some problem and need attention. fatal(3) - VPM card is not functional. offLine(4) - VPM card is in off-line maintenance state.

hh3cVPMResourceUtilization.name: hh3cVPMResourceUtilization
hh3cVPMResourceUtilization.description: The object indicates the percentage of current DSP resource utilization of the VPM card. The utilization is a ratio of number of busy DSP resources (for handling calls, transcoding, voice compression,...) to the total available DSP resources.

hh3cVPMHiWaterUtilization.name: hh3cVPMHiWaterUtilization
hh3cVPMHiWaterUtilization.description: The object indicates the highest percentage of DSP resource utilization of the VPM card that have been occured.

hh3cVPMMaxChannel.name: hh3cVPMMaxChannel
hh3cVPMMaxChannel.description: The maximum number of channels can be supported in each VPM card.

hh3cDSPStatusTable.name: hh3cDSPStatusTable
hh3cDSPStatusTable.description: The table contains status parameters of DSP(Digital Signal Processing) card.

hh3cDSPStatusEntry.name: hh3cDSPStatusEntry
hh3cDSPStatusEntry.description: The entry of DSP status table.

hh3cDSPIndex.name: hh3cDSPIndex
hh3cDSPIndex.description: The index for this entry. DSP is fixed on VPM card or chassis card. The sequence of DSP in the VPM card or chassis card is from right to left.

hh3cDSPVPMIndex.name: hh3cDSPVPMIndex
hh3cDSPVPMIndex.description: The object corresponds to VPMIndex in the chassis. If value of this object is non-zero, it is the index of VPM card.(DSP is in this VPM card.) If value of this object is 0, then the DSP is fixed in the chassis card.

hh3cDSPEnPhysicalIndex.name: hh3cDSPEnPhysicalIndex
hh3cDSPEnPhysicalIndex.description: The object corresponds to PhysicalIndex in the chassis.

hh3cDSPResetTime.name: hh3cDSPResetTime
hh3cDSPResetTime.description: The value of sysUpTime from the last DSP reset occurred.

hh3cDSPMaxChannel.name: hh3cDSPMaxChannel
hh3cDSPMaxChannel.description: The maximum number of channels can be supported in each DSP. The value is chosen in an implementation-dependent manner by the DSP functionality.

hh3cDSPState.name: hh3cDSPState
hh3cDSPState.description: The object indicates the current state of DSP being monitored. normal(1) - DSP in normal condition. fatal(3) - DSP is not functional. offLine(4) - DSP is in off-line maintenance state.

hh3cDSPInUseChannel.name: hh3cDSPInUseChannel
hh3cDSPInUseChannel.description: The number of channels that are reserved for serving calls. The value is incremented when the DSP channel is reserved for call setup and is decremented after the DSP channel is free due to call disconnection.

hh3cVPMStateChange.name: hh3cVPMStateChange
hh3cVPMStateChange.description: This trap is sent when VPM state changes.

hh3cDSPStateChange.name: hh3cDSPStateChange
hh3cDSPStateChange.description: This trap is sent when DSP state changes.
